name: Domino's Pizza
address: Jl. Raya Batubulan, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
i came here for a quick takeout
it only took 10-15 minutes, and the pizza is freshly made in front of you
review 2: Small place, pizza is not best and small(but we bought large). Service is ok
review 3:
Pizza was fine but the place is congested to dine in. Better to take out from there.
Pizza taste is fine and standard as per Domino's standards.

Love the pizza and the service, friendly staff

The girl on counter is quite polite and good to attending outsider like me.

She teach me how to use coins in Bali :D
review 4:
I bought pizza by app
Its take a long time to deliver
When i checked the app, it show the pizza was already delivered
I don't mind to wait but i don't apreciate dishonesty
review 5: Ordered via grab waited over 1.5 hours just for the order to keep getting delayed for them to say it‚Äôs then been delivered but nothing arrived! Wouldn‚Äôt even provide me with the drivers details to contact! Will never be ordering again. Do not recommend

name: Barong & Kris Dance Jambe Budaya
address: 97J5+HVP, Gg. Batu Mutiara No.5, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80582, Indonesia
review 1: It was interesting. Approximately an hour or so long. At times it was a little boring so you really need to like this sort of thing. It was also a little more expensive than I thought $15 Australian dollars per person.
review 2: The customs are nice. It‚Äôs a cultural experience , very traditional. It‚Äôs more about enjoying the live music and the acts. Don‚Äôt expect to understand every single thing they do. They give you a paper with some explanations of the acts. Comfortable large seats and good art. Not a bad experience.
review 3:
Highly recommended. Excellent performance by the performing team which got the crowd fully entrenched. The musicians were also really good.

The theater is open air and very well ventilated by the fans. The high ceilings helps in keeping the place cool. Guests sits on concrete seats laid out like stairs. The employees were all friendly and accomodative hence a plus point to the overall experience.
review 4: Very cool play about the story of Barong and Rangda (good and evil). I won't spoil the rest, fun play to see! Takes around 1:15h or so and started around 9:30 for us.
review 5: The Barong and Keris Dance performance everyday on 09.30 am. When you have day trip to Ubud and surounding,you can stop for awhile to see this traditional dance. Ticket price is IDR 150k/person. Duration for an hour.  Location at Batubulan village,about 1 hour ride from Kuta,Seminyak.

name: Pizza Hut Delivery - PHD Indonesia
address: Jl. Raya Batubulan, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
This is how my delivery arrived. Cold and dry
The rider didn‚Äôt have food warmer bag

Had bad tummy for 2 days after eating here
review 2:
We were looking for vegetarian options and we got 2-3 veg options, cheese lovers, veggie delight and Margherita pizza. All were perfectly baked and tasty.
They also serve long Loma Pizza with 6 different toppings combinationa. Quard pizza was option variant but they did not allow changing the toppings so we did not try it
review 3: One of the fast food restaurants near home, recommended for take away the food cause not too large space here.
review 4:
We have ordered by Grab app when we were travelling in Bali.they cancel the order after changing delivery time for couple of times.they didn't even say sorry .
Their pizzas are pretty good though.
review 5:
They just have samples of drink that they don't have. Complicated to communicate with the staff.  No dinner for us, we went to Domino's.
Thanks

name: The Swaha Hotel
address: Jl. Pasekan Jl. Raya Banjar Tubuh No.29B, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80582, Indonesia
review 1: I slept very well here. Surprisingly quiet, A/C works well, the pool was glorious, and got to chat with the kind and helpful owner. Lovely family-run oasis on the way to everywhere in Bali.
review 2: The rooms are very well cared for. Additionally the owner and the staff are very accommodating as they will stock items if asked. The staff and owner are also very helpful and knowledgeable on Bali and will willfully give inspiration on what to do for the day. The food is delicious. However you might have difficulties finding the hotel as it is located in a small alley
review 3: Rooms are very clean, staff is very friendly and helpful, the hotel is a bit hidden.
review 4: The hotel is good especially for honeymooners because the place is very quiet. The food in the hotel is delicious. you can also cook since the room has mini kitchen. And the staff are very polite as well as the owner. I would really recommend this hotel even though the place is away from the city. They have motorcycle and van if you want to ride around the place. And has free shuttle ride going to market and other selected places.
review 5: Zoo travelers look no further! Great bang for your buck. 10min from the Zoo and Bird park. No dirty smells nice big clean hot showers. Kitchen was handy for morning coffee and evening cups of tea. Food was yummy, staff were friendly and helpful got me discounted rates for zoo admission . The owner even gave me a cheap ride back to airport. I did Bali on a budget and The Swaha certainly didn't break the bank . Best place i stayed in Bali. Thank you Swaha and crew u deserve every point on each of the 5 stars .

name: Mie Pangsit Medan Djoe Djoe
address: Jalan Raya Batubulan Sukawati Gianyar, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
Delicious! Loved the texture of the noodles, Bakso and Ayam/Babi went really well together with everything else. Great place for Mie Pangsit

On the pricier side
review 2: I am looking for the best medan noodles in Bali. I have high expectations towards this. But the pork noodle is too sweet. The noodle itself is just about right. Also, the meatball (idk it is a chicken or pork meatball), I don't like it. The per portion is around 25-40k.
review 3: The best Bakmie Medan in Bali so far. I really like the texture and the taste. The portion is fair enough and the price is very affordable. I ordered Bakmie Pangsit Babi (Noodles with dumpling and pork) (normal portion) and iced orange which costed 31k in total. You can ask to swap the fried dumpling with the boiled one.
review 4:
Noodle lovers must not miss this place.
Located in between Ubud and Southern Bali area, since I found it I've had them as my weekly routine.
Bakmi Pangsit Babi Jumbo everytime I'm there!
You can feel the homey setting as you sat down and of course you can feel the family vibes between the owner and their staff.
review 5: Another pork noodle i can find in Bali. The taste is really good, but the noodle thickness is just not my type, i prefer like thinner noodles. Toppings were good. Like it

name: Babi Kriuk Men Nita
address: Jl. Batu Intan Utama, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80582, Indonesia
review 1: Just simply exceptional. For the amazingly cheap price of Rp25k you would get a generous portion of meal complete with a variety of Balinese pork cooking. Their crispy pork belly, which is the main highlight of the spot, is also delicious and cheaper than what you'll get from other places. Will definitely go here again
review 2:
Very good and tasty "Babi kriuk" - komplet ! (Crispy porc meet dish,  Balinese style) served by a friendly staff. Clean place, quick service and very reasonable prices.  Parking for your car or motorbike nearby.
The place is always good for a fast lunch or dinner or take-away.
Non-halal food! (Sorry Muslims but you will miss something). It is spicy (especially the soup - includes banana-tree vegetables and meet-bones - yummy - you are getting along - tourist take care üî•üå∂Ô∏èüå∂Ô∏èüå∂Ô∏è) - but it is a must if you pass by. You should try also extra sosis uratan and  babi kriuk (meet cuts). My wife found that the dishes and the portions you get in the service at your place have improved. Keep on like this.
Suksema, thanks, staff Babi Kriuk - suka sekali. Also as Take way always a good choice (got really well served - üôèüôèüôè)
---- did it again, so yummy
review 3:
One of hidden gem in ubud. I ordered their babi kriuk set. It served with rice, lawar, babi kecap, babi kriuk, and balungan soup. Everything tasted good. Especially their babi kriuk. I ordered additional 1 portion of their babi kriuk since it tasted really good.

Overall, worth to try. And. For the price, it is totally worthed, since it only costs 20k for thr rice set, and 15k for babi kriuk. Maybe the - point of this place is, it was really hot there. No AC, or even fan there.
review 4:
25k for meal with crispy pork belly.
Very glut.
review 5:
I come to this place from a reference from IG reels. So it's kinda a gambling
When I got here around 10.30 AM wita it's empty, I thought it's not ready to open,but it's already open.
There is only 1 menu of nasi campur.
They served fast, 1 portion of nasi campur is 22.000 rupiah
The portion is enough for me, but for some people may say it quite small. It contain of crispy pork belly, sausage like lapchiong, crispy pork skin and vegetables called lawar. The lawar is quite spicy but overall it is so delicious.
The crispy pork belly and pork skin is realy crispy. The sausage also delicious, not like the the sausage on babi guling menu
Should go to this warung again next time go to gianyar

name: Kopi Kenangan - Ruko Batubulan
address: Jl. Raya Batubulan, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1: This is one of Kopi Kenangan outlets with the best baristas ever. The flavour and composition of each ingredient are always well maintained. Thank you!
review 2: i love how the ambience make me calm n so happy whenever i come
review 3: good ambience and vibe, good drink but will be better if there‚Äôs wifiüòÑ
review 4:
The female barista is very rude.
I don‚Äôt understand how people like her even have job when there are many more kind and deserving people.
We are friendly people‚Ä¶ Just ordering a coffee like anyone else, but she rolled her eyes at us and gave us a bad attitude for no reason.
Not only one time, but also the previous time‚Ä¶ Still acting like a teenage bully.üòÇ

No doubt‚Ä¶ 100%‚Ä¶ She is rude.

review 5:

name: Gogo Fried Chicken Batubulan
address: Jl. Raya Batubulan No.339X, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
Chance upon this local fried chicken shop so came in to try. Their chicken is similar to KFC. It‚Äôs rather good, juicy with crispy skin. I also got the sosro fruit tea, it is good, not very sweet.
If you want you can get it with rice. Take away also cost an additional rp1k.
Came on a Saturday afternoon.
Price: One price chicken rp11k fruit tea rp5k
review 2: The shop was located on a busy street and easy to find. I ordered my food from grabfood and I picked it up myself. The taste of the fried chicken was nice and juicy enough. Definitely a good local fast food place that is worth your visit.
review 3:
Tasty as always

But google location is different. You have to move more forward around 1 km then you'll see the sign "go go chicken" on the left side of the road if you move from Ubud.
review 4: The best ‚ÄúSambal Geprek‚Äù, always order their Goprex. affordable price fried chicken but the taste is supper yummy!
review 5: The chicken is crumbly, the rice is ok, the tea is good, but it's way too expensive compared to the  ACK across the street.

name: Juice Time Batubulan
address: Jl. Raya Batubulan, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80582, Indonesia
review 1: Good quality of food. Everybody will be able to choose something for himself. Cheap if you gonna look at prices in other restaurants. Only one thing with I would change is menu - mixed English and Indonesian language, but with translation was quite easy to get it right and choose something. Cause of good prices and food quality - 5 stars from me.
review 2:
Love this place! The best in the area. The food is tasty and the staff is really nice.

I was just shocked by a customer near me - a woman with a child. The music from the phone of a child was even louder than the music in the cafe. And the woman did not tell him anything üò∞ you are in a public place, it is very ill-mannered
review 3: This is my absolute favorite cafe when i hang out with my friend. The food is always fantastic especially the chocolate cake that always have a perfect taste. The ambiance is very welcoming and charming. There is indoor and outdoor area and backyard for children too. The price was affordable. The service i received was so amazing and we will definitely be back again. I recommended to everyone! I'd like to come here again and again
review 4: Service time can be better.. Love the salad, we liked it, recommended! there is parking area, very cramped, but it's there.. price is affordable.
review 5: The food is actually good especially if you dine in. But when you start ordering from gojek/grab, they lost their consistency. From the packaging and the food quality. I had to complain so many times through grab because either they cook wrong food or the quality so bad . Not to mention the packaging üòëü´†  Just like today, ordered nasi goreng kampung but they gave me nasi goreng kecombrang

name: Ayam Goreng Asli Prambanan Batubulan
address: Jalan Raya Batubulan No.11B, Batubulan, Ubud, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
Pro : price, portion
Cons : none

Price : 4/5 (consider cheap)
Taste : 3.5/5
Cleanliness : 4/5

Tips : it is a local fried chicken specialty resto. Taste is so so but price is cheap for resto in Bali.
review 2:
Good cheap place with yummy food. Nice prices. Lovely stuff. Place is clean. Good options for food and drinks. Place is popular and could be crowdy. At Ayam Goreng Prambanan exist delivery service.
Possible to smoke inside. That's why not recommended for visit with children.
review 3:
I ordered pecel lele (catfish with sambal) and cah kangkung (kangkung soup) this noon. The service was fast, and foods were tasty. I would recommend this restaurant to have a dedicated room for smoking, so that all other visitors won't get exposure with this behaviour.

Parking area is also small. Got a difficulty to take my motorbike out of the park, as there were 3 cars blocked my way.
review 4: Really tasty and inexpensive chicken. Do recommend a lot
review 5: Interesting local chicken rice dinner meal.

name: Sambal Gami Cheff Yogi
address: Jl. Raya Batubulan No.110B, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80582, Indonesia
review 1: If you are on your way to Ubud or Kuta, stop and taste anything from their menu, it‚Äôs jus amazing and super cheap! Love it
review 2: There are various sambal and seafood menus. The taste served is also delicious, just a little sweet in my opinion. the place is comfortable and nice to hang out in while enjoying the menu.
review 3:
It's my first time giving a "meh" rating for a restaurant. First, "sambal gami" definitely not my favorite taste, the smokey taste felt too much like burnt stuff on my tongue. The service is flawless and fast. But the tables is painted in sticky varnish, that really bother my skin, felt like I'm touching a dirty furniture.
Well, that's my personal experience, your mileage may vary.
review 4:
- The food is soooooo good!
- They serve pork so it's not halal
- The sambal matah is literally chefs kiss. You must order it!
- The staff is friendly!
- The price is cheap and definitely reasonable

My go to order is urutan sambal merah + jamur krispi
Will definitely go back again!

name: Warung Wenten Babi Guling
address: 97H4+V4P, Jl. Raya Batubulan, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80237, Indonesia

review 2:
Yummy! Very reccomended!
can hardly wait to eat here again
review 4: its just more pricier than the menu i saw
review 5: The place might be not the cleanest you would expect but the food is good. Take away is advised

address: Jl. Batu Intan III No.1X, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80582, Indonesia
review 1:
Nice place to visit if you want to take yakiniku cuisine in Gianyar. The taste is good and flavorfully,,, the meat is marinated well, the lettuce is really fresh. But the portion is a bit small.
Really recommended for "couple date" or family dinner.
review 2: first time i been here, food was really good and yummy.. i give 4 * for service cause the waitress served all my order in 1 time.. i told to served our Naan first, but overall was good.. will come back again next..
review 3:
The bbq was really good and i enjoyed it the pork belly and the yakiniku sauce is really great and the staff is very friendly too.

Gonna come back again for the pork ribs, thank you so much.
review 4: Quality of food is great, price and portion are fair. Recommended place!
review 5: Very nice Japanese restaurant in Batubulan. Service from Lala made it even better. Makasih üôèüèª

name: Bakso Solo Moro Seneng IV
address: 97H4+Q42, Jl. Raya Batubulan, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
1. The parking space is pretty spacious (It will be a bit tricky if you bring a car but if you bring a motorcycle, there is plenty of room)
2. The bakso taste good however if you prefer bakso urat with a more meaty and "urat" texture you might not like it because the bakso is more "halus" than "urat".

4. They don't afford cashless option so you need to prepare cash if you want to eat here
review 2: Good simple food with very affordable  price.
